Philippine Stocks: Aboitiz Power, Atlas Consolidated Mining

-- B y   C e c i l i a   Y a p
-- 
2011-06-28T04:53:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/philippine-stocks-aboitiz-power-atlas-consolidated-mining.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in Manila.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index gained 0.70, or 0.02
percent, to 4,289.99.  Aboitiz Power Corp. (AP)   rose 0.5 percent to 30.75
pesos, its highest level since June 17. The company, an
electricity generator and retailer, said it may partner with
Manila Electric Co. to build a 600-megawatt power plant in
Zambales province.  Atlas Consolidated Mining & Development (AT)  Corp rose
1.8 percent to 20.35 pesos, its highest close since May 21,
2007. Chairman Alfredo Ramos said the company expects to reach a
deal with a potential investor within the week.  “There’s an investor coming that’s going to help the
company realize its potential,” Astro del Castillo, managing
director at Manila-based First Grade Holdings Inc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cecilia Yap in  Manila  at 
 cyap19@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  